After that, the UV spectra of N-CDs in the presence and absence of FEN were investigated. The two spectra show high similarity, as shown in Fig. 5e. This result denies the formation of a ground state complex between N-CDs and FEN. Therefore, the static mechanism was further excluded [56,57]. Finally, the fluorescence lifetime (t1
                        ) of the N-CDs before and after the addition of FEN was measured, as shown in Fig. 5f. The fluorescence lifetime (t1
                        ) of N-CDs was 2.44 ns. In the presence of FEN, it remained nearly unchanged (2.43 ns). This further excludes the dynamic quenching and confirms that the quenching originated from IFE only [58,59].
